MAC_MODE_HFM - Static variable in class com.trendit.basesdk.device.pinpad.PINPadConstants
Hypercom Fast Mode perform bitwise XOR on BLOCK1 and BLOCK2, and perform bitwise XOR on the XOR result and BLOCK3, sequentially, to obtain an 8-byte (or 16-byte) XOR result.
MAC_MODE_TDES_ECB - Static variable in class com.trendit.basesdk.device.pinpad.PINPadConstants
 
MAC_MODE_X919 - Static variable in class com.trendit.basesdk.device.pinpad.PINPadConstants
According to the ANSIX9.19 specification BLOCK1 is encrypted using TAK for TDES/AES (only the first 8 bytes (or 16 bytes) of keys are taken), and the encryption result is XOR bit by bit with BLOCK2, followed by TAK for DES encryption.
MAC_MODE_X99 - Static variable in class com.trendit.basesdk.device.pinpad.PINPadConstants
Use the MAC key to perform TDES/AES encryption on BLOCK1, perform bitwise XOR on the encryption result with BLOCK2, and then use TAK to perform TDES/AES encryption, sequentially obtaining an encryption result of 8 bytes (or 16 bytes)
